# 🤖 AI Crypto Trading Bot — Project Context & Rules

## Project Overview

This is a **production-grade, self-driving AI cryptocurrency trading bot** for the Binance exchange. It uses a multi-layer AI decision engine (Market Regime Classifier + Temporal Fusion Transformer + RL Agent + Sentiment Analysis) to autonomously select assets, size positions, manage risk, and execute trades. The bot manages a USDT budget of $500–$5,000 and trades spot pairs on Binance.

**This is real-money software. Every line of code has financial consequences.**

---

## 🏗️ Architecture Overview

```
data/ingestion/       → WebSocket + REST data collection (Binance, CoinGecko, news)
data/processing/      → Feature engineering (50+ TA indicators, NLP sentiment)
data/storage/         → TimescaleDB (persistence) + Redis (real-time cache)
models/               → Regime classifier, TFT, RL agent, FinBERT sentiment
strategy/             → Universe selection, signal aggregation, portfolio optimization
risk/                 → Risk manager, position sizer, circuit breakers
execution/            → Order manager, Binance executor, fee optimizer
monitoring/           → Grafana, Telegram alerts, performance tracking
backtesting/          → Event-driven engine, walk-forward validation
pipeline/             → Auto-retraining, drift detection, meta-learning
api/                  → FastAPI control interface
```

---

## 🛑 Critical Rules — Never Violate

### Financial Safety
- **NEVER place a real order without passing through `RiskManager.validate()`** — this is the single gate that prevents catastrophic losses
- **NEVER hardcode API keys, secrets, or credentials** — always use `config/settings.py` which reads from environment variables only
- **NEVER allow withdrawal permissions on the Binance API key** — trade-only permissions only
- **NEVER skip the backtesting gate** — no strategy or model goes live without passing `backtesting/walk_forward.py` validation
- **NEVER trade more than 2% of total portfolio value on a single position** — this is enforced in `risk/risk_manager.py`
- **NEVER deploy 100% of budget** — always keep 20% as USDT reserve

### Code Quality
- **NEVER use synchronous code in the data ingestion layer** — everything must be `async/await` using `asyncio`
- **NEVER catch bare `Exception` without logging the full stack trace and context**
- **NEVER store state in global variables** — use dependency injection or the database
- **NEVER mutate a DataFrame in-place** — always use `df.copy()` or return new DataFrames
- **NEVER use `time.sleep()` in async code** — use `asyncio.sleep()`

### Data Integrity
- **NEVER use future data in feature calculation** — this causes look-ahead bias and invalidates all backtesting
- **NEVER write to the `candles` table without the upsert conflict handler** — duplicate timestamps will corrupt the dataset
- **NEVER assume WebSocket data is continuous** — always check for gaps before calculating indicators

